Checks if two objects of the same class are identical having some properties included. The method compares all properties of both objects. If any of these properties has a different value, then the method returns false. If all properties of both objects are equal, then the method returns true.

alike

public static <T> boolean alike(T left,
                                T right,
                                java.lang.String... propertiesToCompare)
Checks if two objects look alike, in the sense that they have some of their properties equal. The method compares some properties of both objects. If any of these properties has a different value, then the method returns false. If all properties of both objects are equal, then the method returns true. The properties are specified in the method.

Type Parameters:
T - Type of objects being compared.
Parameters:
left - First element to compare.
right - Second element to compare.
propertiesToCompare - Array with strings that contains the properties of the objects that should be compared.
Returns:
Returns true if the objects are same excluding the specified properties. Otherwise returns false.

alike

public static <T> boolean alike(java.util.Set<T> left,
                                java.util.Set<T> right,
                                java.lang.Class<T> clazz,
                                java.lang.String keyProperty,
                                java.lang.String[] propertiesToCompare)
Checks if two sets look alike, in the sense that they contain fields which are one by one alike. The method matches all objects of the two sets in pairs, according to a key property. All elements of both pairs must much, otherwise the method returns false. If all elements match, then the method compares all pairs, trying to match their elements with the alike(T left, T right, String... pralikeopertiesToCompare) method. If all pairs have elements which are alike with each other, then the method returns true, otherwise the method returns false.

Type Parameters:
T - Type of objects being compared.
Parameters:
left - First set.
right - Second set.
keyProperty - Name of the property that contains the matching key
propertiesToCompare - Properties used to find if the objects are alike.
clazz - Type of objects being compared.
Returns:
Returns true if all objects in the left and right sets match according to their key property and are alike having in pairs the specified properties equal.
See Also:
alike(Object, Object, String...)
